title: Twin Blasts in Turkish Capital Kill at Least 95 People
text:
Twin Blasts in Turkish Capital Kill a... Twin Blasts in Turkish Capital Kill at Least 95 People 11 hrs ago Read more: Wall Street Journal 
Scores of people were killed in the Turkish capital, Ankara, early Saturday after two explosions occurred outside the city's train station. At least 95 people were killed in twin blasts in the Turkish capital on Saturday, as the deadliest terror attack in the country's modern history laid bare the precarious security environment just three weeks before snap elections .
